<body>

  

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🥙 Soft & Fluffy Chapati Recipe</h1>
       

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups Whole Wheat Flour (Atta)</li>
            <li>¾ cup Water (adjust as needed)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Oil or Ghee</li>
            <li>½ tsp Salt</li>
            <li>Extra Flour (for dusting)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>In a bowl, mix wheat flour and salt.</li>
            <li>Gradually add water and knead into a soft dough.</li>
            <li>Add oil and knead for another 5 minutes until smooth.</li>
            <li>Cover the dough and let it rest for 20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Divide into small balls and roll each into a thin circle.</li>
            <li>Heat a tawa or pan and cook chapati on medium heat.</li>
            <li>Flip when bubbles appear and cook both sides until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Brush with ghee (optional) and serve hot with curry.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
